==English==
===Etymology===
This phrase was invented because someone thought it sounded cool.
===Verb===
'''Exit Stage Left'''
#{{computing}} the process of logging out and immediately logging back in.  Usually to fix an inexplicable error.
#:''After I '''Exited Stage Left''' I was able to...''
#:''Just '''Exit Stage Left''' and you should be able to...''

